This paper is about Android malware detection using deep learning, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also utilizes natural language processing techniques, which could potentially place it in the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of bi-directional Long Short Term Memory networks, which is a type of recurrent neural network, placing it in the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the feature extraction method used to derive behavior sequences from Android applications, which could potentially place it in the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
